  "stem": "<p>In the <em>xy</em>-plane, the graphs of the equations <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> and <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math> intersect at two points. Which of the following is one of those points?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p>(0, 4)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p>(4, 4)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p>(-4, 4)</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p>(4, -4)</p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "b"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Setting the two expressions equal gives <math><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>, or <math><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></math>. So <math><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, giving <em>x</em> = 0 or <em>x</em> = 4. When <em>x</em> = 4, <em>y</em> = 4, so (4, 4) is an intersection point.</p><p>Choices A, C, and D are incorrect.</p>",
